[[File:Garcinia indica syrup making from rinds.jpg|thumb|left|The vessel on the left contains syrup which is obtained from the vessel containing kokum rinds, on the right. The syrup is used to make kokum sherbet]]

'''''Solam''''' are skins of fruits like the birondd (Garcinia Indica , sometimes called the “wild mangosteen”)
and peelings of the mango, dried in the sun, and sometimes cured in salt. The solam
are used as condiments in curries and sauces.



